cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the optimisation of networked embedded systems.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the scheduling and optimisation of real-time systems.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses communication routing and arbitration in networked embedded systems.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses the allocation and scheduling of tasks in distributed systems.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of evolutionary approaches to optimise software systems.
